data.TEXT: Change-Management in verwalteten Systemen (Administrator)
Change Management on managed systems (Administrator)
This role is used for Change Management functionalities on managed systems.
For more information/description of the role and authorizations, see
Security Guide for SAP Solution Manager on the Service Marketplace
at: http://service.sap.com/instguides -> SAP Components -> SAP
Solution Manager <current release>
SAP Solution Manager <current release>
First version SAP Solution Manager 7.1 SP01 (delivered ST-PI 2008_1_700 SP04)
Last changed SAP Solution Manager ST-PI 740 SP08
Note:
Full authorization for fields (due to use in work center SAP Solution
Manager Configuration; Transaction SOLMAN_SETUP)
History:
SP08
- added FUNC SPROJECT_TR_PROJECT_EXIST_R, SPROJECT_TR_PROJECT_RENAME_R in
authorization object S_RFC (These Function Modules are called on the managed
system side when you execute reports called with transaction
/TMWFLOW/ASSIGN_IMG on the Solution Manager system side)
SP06
- added S_CTS_SADM (for more information, check Security Guide)
SP05
- added FUNC values TR_LOG_OVERVIEW_REQ and  _SATC_CI_CRR_DISPLAY_RESULT to
authorization object S_RFC
SP03
- added values FUNC TMW_CHANGE_PROJECT_SETTING, TR_LOG_OVERVIEW_REQUEST_REMOTE
to S_RFC
SP02
- substituted FUGR with FUNC in authorization object S_RFC
- added FUNC TMW_MODIFY_COMM to S_RFC (Enable Trans/ALL user to modify TR
details, like change owner of a TR)
SP09
- added value SCCA for authoriaztion object S_RFC (required for project
creation)
SP06
- all fields which contain no specific values are delivered with asterisks (*)
SP05
- added FUGR value TMWB_REQUESTS to authorization object S_RFC
- added authorization object S_PROJECT with ACTVT 03 (display)
- added additional values STPA, SEMM_UTIL, STRH, TR_CTS_PROJECTS,
TRWB_REQUESTS,SCW2,SCW0,SVRW, BFHV (for QGM) to authorization object S_RFC
